    "visualization_explanation": "The dataset contains two time-series variables across 12 monthly intervals: raw sales figures (discrete quantitative) and moving average (continuous quantitative). Synthetic sales data (\u03bc=163.3k, \u03c3=25.9k) follows seasonal retail patterns with Q4 peak, while the moving average (\u03bc=158.9k, \u03c3=14.7k) applies a 12-month smoothing window. Data ranges maintain retail plausibility through industry benchmarks.\n\nThe combination chart maximizes data-ink ratio by encoding primary metric as columns (precise value comparison) and trend as spline (continuous pattern). Cairo's principles are applied through color contrast (blue=primary metric, red=derived measure) and proportional encoding. The dual-axis approach maintains temporal alignment while preventing scale distortion, with gridline reduction minimizing visual noise."
